x,y \in \mathbb{R}
0<p<\infty
|x-y|^p\leq (1+2^p)(|x|^p+|y|^p) 
0<p\leq1
P:=1/p
1<p<\infty
|x-y|^p=|x-y|^{1/P}\leq |x|^{1/P} + |y|^{1/P} = |x|^{p} + |y|^{p} \leq (1+2^p)(|x|^p+|y|^p)
1<p<\infty
\left|x-y\right|^p \leq \left( |x|+|y|\right)^p \leq 2^p\left(\frac{1}{2}\left|x\right|^p + \frac{1}{2}\left|2y\right|^p \right)= 2^{p-1}(|x|^p+|y|^p) \leq (1+2^p)(|x|^p+|y|^p)
